      "rationale": "Nominal values for all 13 model inputs (geometry, boundary conditions, fluid properties, hemolysis model constants) sourced from calibrated measurements or literature. Input uncertainty ranges defined and propagated via 256-sample LHS. The UQ analysis quantified output NIH variability across the input space. A screening sensitivity study was conducted as part of the UQ workflow and identified flow rate and rotational speed as the dominant contributors to NIH variance; these findings are documented in internal technical report TR-2024-CPB-07. The structured sensitivity analysis artefact is referenced narratively here and the UQ propagation results confirm that input uncertainty is bounded within the validation uncertainty envelope."
