    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per the credibility plan. Uncertainty quantification has been performed and demonstrates that output NIH variability remains within the validation uncertainty envelope across the defined input space. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 is confirmed at all five operating points. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model provides sufficient credibility evidence to support the regulatory decision for the Class II CPB device submission.",
